<TABLE BGCOLOR="#FF0000" >
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="3"><B><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><FONT SIZE=+2>PPP »P SLIP ¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@</FONT></FONT></B></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>SLIP</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>Serial Line IP (RFC 1055)</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Encapsulation for IP packets on serial lines (Data link
protocol)</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>IP addresses must be assigned to two end systems <BR>
before connection</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>no type field: only supports IP</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>no CRC check</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>framming: co + data + co</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>avoid &quot;co&quot; by &quot;db dc&quot;</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>avoid &quot;db&quot; by &quot;db dd&quot;</FONT></LI>
</UL>
</UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>PPP</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>RFC 1661, RFC 1662, RFC 1663</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>Features</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>correct all the deficiencies in SLIP</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>support multiple network-layer protocols (IP=0x0021,
<BR>
LCP=0xc021, NCP=0x8021)</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>CRC check</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Dynamic negotation of IP addresses</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Header compression</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Authentication</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>Provides</FONT></LI>
<UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>framming: 7e + data + 7e</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>avoid &quot;7e&quot; by &quot;7d 5e&quot;</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>avoid &quot;7d&quot; by &quot;7d 5d&quot;</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>avoid control code (less than 20) by &quot;7d 21+code&quot;</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Link Control Protocol (LCP) for bringing lines up, testing
them, negotiating options, and bringing down gracefully when done.
</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1> Network Control Protocol (NCP) for different network
layer protocol support, such as negotation of IP address.
</FONT></LI>

</UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2></FONT>Connection Management</LI>
<UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Start up: </FONT></LI>
<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1> A series of LCP packets is sent to negotiate PPP options.
</FONT></LI>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1> NCP is used to do the IP address assignment.
</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Tear Down:</FONT></LI>
<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1> NCP is used to tear down network layer connection and
free up IP address.
</FONT></LI>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1> LCP is used to shutdown data link layer connection.
</FONT></LI>
</UL>

</UL>

<IMG SRC="PPPstate.gif">

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2></FONT>PPP Packet Format</LI>
<IMG SRC="pppformat.gif">
<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Address: set to 11111111 for broadcast.</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Control: 00000011 for unnumbered frame</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Address and control are constant in default setting,
a PPP option is to skip these two fields.</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+1>Protocol: protocol type identifies LCP, NCP, IP, IPX, ....
Starts with &quot;0&quot; bit for network layer protocols, 
&quot;1&quot; bit for negotiation.
</FONT></LI>
</UL>

</UL>
</UL>

<TABLE BGCOLOR="#FF0000" >
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="3"><B><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><FONT SIZE=+2>ISO ªººô¸ô¼h¨ó©w:
X.25 ¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@</FONT></FONT></B></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>X.21 -- layer 1, LAP, LPAB -- layer 2, X.25 -- layer
3</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>Connection oriented</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>two types of virtual circuits</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>permanent</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>on demand (requested/cleared)</FONT></LI>
</UL>
</UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>Addressing</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>14 decimal digits, BCD encoded (4 bits each digit, <BR>
56 bits totally)</FONT></LI>
</UL>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>Packet format</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>12-bit virtual circuit number (logic group number <BR>
+ logic channel number)</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>3-bit sequence number</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>3-bit acknowledge number</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>a more bit to indicate the last packet in a long<BR>
message</FON

<LI>default max. data is 128 bytes</FONT></LI>
</UL>
</UL>

<TABLE BGCOLOR="#FF0000" >
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="3"><B><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><FONT SIZE=+2>ISO ªººô¸ô¼h¨ó©w:
CLNP ¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@¡@</FONT></FONT></B></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>ConnectionLess Network Protocol</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>functionally equivalent to IP</FONT></LI>

<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>packet format</FONT></LI>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=+2>version, id, address, flags, qos, fragment offset,<BR>
header length, TTL, packet length, options</FONT></LI>
</UL>
</UL>

